Package ms.ipp.iterator

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CustomDeleteIterator<T>
    A Decorator for an Iterator<T> allowing to call a custom hook immediately before a current element is deleted in the remove()-method.
    EmptyIterator<T>
    This Iterator has no elements
    FilteredIterator<T>
    Filtering iterator with the ability to remove filtered elements.
    FilteredSpliterator<T>
    A Decorator for an Spliterator<T> which only shows those elements, for which a given filter returns true.
    MappedIterator<T,R>
    A Decorator for an Iterator<T> which maps every element from T to R by means of a given mapping function.
    MappedSpliterator<T,R>
    A Decorator for a Spliterator<T> which maps every element from T to R by means of a given mapping function.
    NestedIterator<T,U>
    An Iterator which offers a "flattened-up" view on hierarchical structures with two levels.
    OneIterator<F>
    An iterator containing exactly one element.
